  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>Familiarity with the military traditions of your homeland inspires uncommon valor in you.</em><br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>You gain a +2 bonus on all saving throws against fear effects. Whenever a fear effect targets you and fails to affect you (either because of a successful saving throw or because of immunity to fear), you gain a +2 morale bonus on attack rolls, weapon damage rolls, and CMB checks against the creature that attempted to use the fear affect on you for 1 round.<br/><br/><b>Combat Trick</b><br/>You can spend 2 stamina points in order to gain the benefit of Focused Discipline for 1 round as if you had been targeted by a fear effect that failed to affect you.",
